AGI -&nbsp;It began with a procession in the city of Tabriz, capital of the province of East Azerbaijan, the funeral ceremony for President Ebrahim Raisi died Sunday in a helicopter crash while traveling right to this city in the northwest of Iran. Raisi, 63 years old, lost his life together with other aircraft passengers, including Foreign Minister Hossein Amirabdollahian.
<br The Iranian supreme leader, the Aytollah Ali Khamenei, proclaimed five days of mourning and appointed interim president Mohammad Mokhber until the new elections scheduled for June 28. The office of Foreign Minister will be occupied by Ali Bagheri, so far Deputy Minister and principal negotiator of the Iranian nuclear programme.
The major state of the Iranian armed forces ordered an investigation into the causes of the incident, reported the ISNA press agency.
&nbsp;
Before the official start of the funeral, meetings were held in different cities of the country in honor of the late President. In Tehran, thousands of people, many of whom with the portrait of Raisi, gathered in Piazza Valiasr. After the funeral procession in Tabriz, Raisi's psalm will be transferred to the holy city of Rom, south of Tehran, and from there will be brought into the capital.<br> Ayatollah Khamenei will guide prayers during a farewell ceremony scheduled in Tehran this evening, before tomorrow the processions begin in the capital. From there, the remains of the deceased president will be transferred Thursday to the province of South Khorasan, in the east, and then to his hometown, Mashhad, where they will be buried in the evening.
